chunk_content: Once implementing partner staff have completed data entry for the reporting period, they should confirm the overall completeness of data by reviewing the DATIM favorites provided by the “MER Result & Target Review” DATIM dashboard that display MER indicators’ “Numerator” value and “Denominator” value by disaggregation totals (e.g., total by age/sex, total by service delivery point/test result, total by age/sex/service type, etc.). If there are data completeness issues, the IP should work to address these problems or acknowledge data completeness limitations within the implementing mechanism indicator performance narrative. Agency Review Process 1. “Accept” data from implementing partner via Data Approvals App. 2. Review data for completeness and accuracy. 3. If data are complete and accurate, “Submit” data to Interagency via Data Approvals App. 4.
